ARETGR is the length of a regular grid which covers
completely the object.
Regular tetrahedra with an edge length ARETGR will be created.

If the User has NOT given the 
DefFunc Taille_Ideale(x,y,z); ...  (as wished length!...)
then
  the tetrahedra with a too great volume will be
  reduced by the introduction of their barycentre.
  Let
  MXED the maximum of edges of the triangles of the object boundary
  MXED the minimum of edges of the triangles of the object boundary

  If ARETGR<MXED, few barycentres will be added
  If ARETGR>2 MXED then ARETGR takes the value MXED
  If ARETGR<MIED   then ARETGR takes the value (MXIN+2MXED)/3
else
  The tetrahedra will be made with edge lengths which
  verify Taille_Ideale(x,y,z)

  This the way to indicate around the point (x,y,z) what
  the length of edges has to be!

Example for the input of Taille_Ideale:

DefVar lxf,lh2,lh3;
lh2=0.3;
lh3=0.7;
lxf=max(lh2,lh3);

DefFunc Taille_Ideale(x,y,z);
  Taille_Ideale=0.45;
  If x<lxf and y>-(lh3+lh2)*1.2
    Then Taille_Ideale=0.15;
  Else
    If x<lxf and y>-(lh3+lh2)*1.8
    Then Taille_Ideale=0.28;
    EndIf;
  EndIf;
EndFunc;
